    <h2 class="lead" id="showGlossaryDiv">About Out of Stock</h2>

    <div id="glossarycontent" class="terminology">
        The Out of Stock (OOS) Tool was developed to help detect out of stock trends, improve ordering and quicken response rates to
        out of stock situations.  Out of Stock items result in lost sales opportunities.  Tracking and monitoring out of stock items
        can help store/regional managers anticipate out of stock events, and take corrective measures to ensure sufficient supply in
        order to meet demand.  This project provides a tool to track and monitor out of stock events and help reduce out of stock
        rates, thereby regaining lost sales.
    </div>


    <br />
    <h3 class="lead" id="showGlossaryDiv">Summary Report</h3>

    The Summary Report will show the out of stock counts/percentages for all stores in your region and the regional averages (located
    at the bottom).  You region will be selected automatically based on your location.
    <br />
    <br />
    You will see all stores in your region listed in the Store Name column.  Store out of stock counts and percentages are displayed
    for Grocery and Whole Body (only for the selected date range).  The number of completed scan sessions during the date range will
    be displayed in the Times Scanned column.
    <br />
    <br />
    At the bottom of the report you will see the regional averages.  When all stores count their out of stocks everyone will be able
    to compare values.  This is a way to view what stores have achieved and know out of stock averages for the entire region.  You can
    use this average by trying to keep your store’s average below the regional average.


