    <h3 class="lead" id="showGlossaryDiv">Custom Report</h3>

    Custom Reports present detailed information about each out of stock item scanned along with status information where available.
    There are two different levels of the Custom Report.  There is a single-store and a multi-store Custom Report.
    <br />
    <br />
    As a suggested business rule, Custom Reports are helpful if they are pulled consistently.  Some regions have suggested they be
    pulled weekly after their Sunday scans.

    <div class="question" id="question">
        <p class="lead">
            <a href="#answer5" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer5')">How to adjust the date range?</a>
        </p>

        <div class="answer" id="answer5" style="display: none">
            <ul class="answer">
                <li>
                    To adjust the date range of the report manually select the FROM and TO dates.  The dates can be from a single day
                    up to one year span.
                </li>
            </ul>
            <br />
            <img src="/Content/images/Support/Select Date Custom Report.JPG" />
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="question" id="question">
        <p class="lead">
            <a href="#answer6" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer6')">What are the formulas for the calculated columns?</a>
        </p>

        <div class="answer" id="answer6" style="display: none">
            <ul class="answer">
                <li>Average Daily Units - Average unit sold per day, over the last 12 weeks, from the last day item sold.</li>
                <li>
                    Cumulative Sales Opportunity - Sales opportunity that is lost due to an out of stock.
                    <br />
                    Single Store Report: Single Day = Movement * Price, Multi-day = Summation of (Movement * Price) per day.
                    <br />
                    Multi- Store Report: Single Day = Summation of (Movement * Price) per store, Multi-day = Summation of (Movement * Price) per store, per day.
                </li>
                <li>Last Date Sold - Last date the item sold.</li>
                <li>Days with Sales - Number of days with sales, over the last 12 weeks, from the last day item sold.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

