        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="question" id="question">
        <p class="lead">
            <a href="#answer9" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer9')">How can the Custom Report help me?</a>
        </p>

        <div class="answer" id="answer9" style="display: none">
            <ul class="answer">
                <li>
                    Custom Reports can help you identify:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Fast-mover out of stocks.</li>
                        <li>Discontinued items that are still tagged.</li>
                        <li>Long term out of stocks that require temporary replacement.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="answer" >
                <li>
                    Check the Custom Report Product Status Column for Updates on items that your store scanned as out of stock.
                    <ul>
                        <li>Replace discontinued items.</li>
                        <li>Update tags for UPC changes.</li>
                        <li>Temporarily replace known long term out of stock items if an alternative SKU is available.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="answer" >
                <li>
                    If you are regularly running out of a product, you may need to:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Adjust ordering.</li>
                        <li>Holding power.</li>
                        <li>Restocking attention in the afternoon/evening.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="answer" >
                <li>
                    Focus your attention on the OOS items that are worth the most money by looking at the Cumulative Sales field.
                    <ul>
                        <li>The Cumulative Sales field is already sorted for you to view highest to lowest potential sales loss.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="answer" >
                <li>
                    Determine average daily movement in the Average Daily Sales column.
                    <ul>
                        <li>If you’re struggling to keep an item in stock and you cannot adjust holding power, this can help you determine appropriate daily pars.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="answer">
                <li>Identify recurring out of stocks by generating a multi-week report and sorting by the Number of Times Scanned field.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>



