    <h3 class="lead" id="showGlossaryDiv">Product Status</h3>
    The OOS Tool allows Regional Users to manage (add, update, remove) an individual status or a group of item statues by using the
    Product Status tab.  Status information will appear in the store’s Custom Reports when the item is scanned as out of stock by
    that store.

    <div class="question" id="question">
        <p class="lead">
            <a href="#answer10" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer10')">What is a Product Status?</a>
        </p>

        <p class="answer" id="answer10" style="display: none">
            A Product Status contains information for the scanned out of stock item.  This is a message the Regional Users want
            to communicate to the Store Users.  This information can come from vendors or someone with knowledge of the product
            and the status of that product.  Items with Status Information will be displayed with the most recent at the top.
            After adding a new item, the new item will appear at the top of the page.  If that item is scanned as out of stock,
            it will appear in that store’s Custom Reports if scanned before the expiration date occurs.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="question" id="question">
        <p class="lead">
            <a href="#answer11" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer11')">Where do I see the Product Status?</a>
        </p>

        <p class="answer" id="answer11" style="display: none">
            You can see the Product Status on the Custom Report.
        </p>
    </div>

