    <div class="question" id="question">
        <p class="lead">
            <a href="#answer16" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer16')">How do I add a multiple Product Status?</a>
        </p>

        <div class="answer" id="answer16" style="display: none">
            The Out of Stock Tool allows regional users to upload bulk product status information that they receive
            from distributors about existing or potential out of stocks.  This status information appears on the
            Custom Reports when an item with status information is scanned as out of stock.  The Bulk Upload tab allows
            regional users to upload a spreadsheet of status information for multiple out of stocks.  A template is
            provided for you, though you can use your own spreadsheet.
            <br />
            <br />
            The Status information entered can be viewed in the Custom Reports when an item is scanned as out of stock.
            If an Expiration Date is not entered it will default to 14 days out from upload date.  You will receive a
            successful confirmation message when the data is uploaded.  You will receive an error message if a missing
            required field is empty or not included in the spreadsheet or if a UPC cannot be identified as a known product.

            <ul class="answer">
                <li>Select the Bulk Upload tab.</li>
                <br />
                <img src="/Content/images/Support/Bulk Upload Template.JPG" />
                <li>Select the link Template.</li>
                <li>This link will open an Excel Spreadsheet.</li>
                <li>Enter UPCs in column A (required field).</li>
                <li>Enter Status information in column B (required field).</li>
                <li>Enter Expiration Date in column C (optional field).</li>
                <li>Save the template to your desktop.</li>
                <li>Select the Browse button in the OOS Tool.</li>
                <li>Select the document you saved to your desktop to upload.</li>
                <li>A confirmation message will be shown.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>





