    <h3 class="lead" id="showGlossaryDiv">Admin</h3>

    The OOS Tool allows Regional Users the ability to manange SKU counts for their departments.  This number is part of the percentage formula
    displayed on the Summary Report.

    <div class="question" id="question">
        <p class="lead">
            <a href="#answer17" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer17')">Who updates the SKU Counts?</a>
        </p>

        <p class="answer" id="answer17" style="display: none">
            All Regional Users have access to this tab. Regions must decide who will update this page and keep it current.
            It could be one person or many people; the main is that the methodology is consistent.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="question" id="question">
        <p class="lead">
            <a href="#answer18" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer18')">How often should the SKUs be updated?</a>
        </p>

        <p class="answer" id="answer18" style="display: none">
            Totals SKU counts should be changed on a quarterly or bi-annual basis to capture impacts due to remodels.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="question" id="question">
        <p class="lead">
            <a href="#answer19" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer19')">How do you get an accurate SKU Count for each store?</a>
        </p>

        <p class="answer" id="answer19" style="display: none">
            Use a 12 week movement report as a generally accurate means of estimating SKU counts by store.  Pull out
            non-retail SKUs (like special order PLUs or coupon PLUs) that should not count towards the total number
            of items store offers for sale at the shelf.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="question" id="question">
        <p class="lead">
            <a href="#answer20" onclick="toggleAnswer('answer20')">How do I enter a department SKU count?</a>
        </p>

        <div class="answer" id="answer20" style="display: none">
            <ul class="answer" >
                <li>Select the Administration tab.</li>
                <li>Enter the SKU count in the field associated with the store and department.</li>
                <li>Select Save Changes button.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>




